    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have no interest in using treesitter, but it is turned on by default for lua files. As far as I can tell, the only way I can disable it is per-buffer with something like this:\n\n```vim\nautocmd FileType lua lua vim.treesitter.stop()\n```\n\nIt seems unnecessary that I have to do this with an autocommand.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCould there be an option, something as simple as `set treesitter=0` that I could set?",
